1
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:25,480
Nice to meet you, Petch.

2
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,080
You can text me anytime.

3
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,640
Can I keep the tickets?

4
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:32,200
PREVIOUSLY

5
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,120
Is this your place?

6
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,360
It's huge,

7
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,400
but I feel so alone.

8
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:38,960
How did that punk tag along?

9
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,440
Let me be frank.

10
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,360
I'm forbidding you
from seeing my daughter.

11
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:45,440
He won't let me go to the concert.

12
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,760
About your dad,

13
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,480
I'll take care of it.

14
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,240
Petch is here?

15
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:53,000
I didn't expect to see you
at a rock concert.

16
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,240
We couldn't find Dao.

17
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:56,960
Tell everyone to find Ms. Dao.

18
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,680
Let's get out of here.

19
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,720
Have you seen Dao?

20
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,000
Keep looking.

21
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,040
What will happen to Dao?

22
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,440
What should we do?

23
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:45,960
I think I should…

24
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,720
I'll drive both of you home.

25
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:52,240
I'll take care of Dao.

26
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:53,600
Okay.

27
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,560
Let's go.

28
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:59,560
FLUKE NOODLE HOUSE

29
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:02,600
Eat some vegetables.

30
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,760
Are you for real?

31
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:07,520
Why? You hate vegetables?

32
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,600
Yes.

33
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:10,160
Look.

34
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:13,040
There are roast red pork, wontons,
and tender noodles.

35
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,920
They're tastier than veggies.

36
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:17,480
This is mine and Dam's go-to spot.

37
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,240
Dam is my friend.

38
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,200
After school and after band practice,

39
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:25,000
we always come to eat noodles here.

40
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:28,440
- Sir, one more bowl, please.
- Yes.

41
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:29,880
All right.

42
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,120
One bowl of wonton noodles, please.

43
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,960
All right.

44
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:36,560
Can you eat all of that?

45
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,960
- Sir.
- Yes.

46
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,120
Make it two, please.

47
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,240
Two, of course.

48
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:43,200
- All right.
- Hey.

49
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,520
You can't waste food.

50
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,400
You're complaining like a grandpa.

51
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,440
I can eat them all.

52
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,120
This is rare.

53
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,760
I should eat as much as I can.

54
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,080
Rare?

55
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,360
Are you out of your mind?

56
00:05:56,880 --> 00:05:57,880
This is rare?

57
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,280
A street vendor like this?

58
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,560
For you, it's ordinary.

59
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,040
But for me,

60
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:08,640
my parents wouldn't allow me
to have noodles from a street vendor.

61
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,000
Strange.

62
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,760
As if we're

63
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:14,960
living in different worlds.

64
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,320
If I am rich in my world,

65
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,920
but I can't be myself,

66
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,600
it's very frustrating.

67
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,240
My world can't beat this.

68
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,040
What was that?

69
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,520
Right.

70
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,840
You can be yourself now.

71
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,480
Thanks.

72
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:34,440
Damn it! I hate being poor!

73
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:38,640
If I were rich,
I wouldn't have to pay my debt.

74
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,920
Come on, bro. Let's go.

75
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,480
Let's have some noodles.

76
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,920
More carbs, more energy.

77
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,840
Yes.

78
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,040
Guys. That's Petch.

79
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,640
It would be better
if I were up there on the stage.

80
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,160
Wait.

81
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,120
Mud.

82
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,200
Akekaphol's right-hand man
sent me a message.

83
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,880
About your debt, perhaps.

84
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:21,080
It's not the due date yet, asshole.

85
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:23,680
You had better read his message.

86
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,600
Right.

87
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:28,000
"If you find the girl in the picture,

88
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,840
contact us immediately.

89
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,760
We have a reward."

90
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:33,039
MUD

91
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:36,720
Hey, that's the girl walking with Petch.

92
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,400
Are you sure you got the right one?

93
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,960
What?

94
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,000
Ms. Natedao was with whom?

95
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,160
Share the location now.

96
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,800
We found her, sir.

97
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,320
Who is she with?

98
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,320
Joe said she is with a man named Petch.

99
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:58,400
Petch.

100
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,960
You stole my girl.

101
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,600
Call Joe.

102
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:03,960
Tell him to beat Petch up.

103
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:04,960
Yes, sir.

104
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,720
Dao.

105
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,160
I forgot what I was going to ask you.

106
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,200
What is it?

107
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:16,160
You said you were being followed.

108
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:17,680
Who was it?

109
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,120
Akekaphol.

110
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,040
He must have told my parents by now.

111
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,360
I can't imagine

112
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:35,040
what would happen when I get home.

113
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,680
Did I cause you trouble?

114
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,520
No.

115
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:49,440
To see the concert with you

116
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:53,600
and eat the best noodles in the world,

117
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,720
I would accept any punishment.

118
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:57,920
You're joking.

119
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
I'm not. I mean it.

120
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,320
It was worth it.

121
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,440
My stomach almost burst.

122
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,400
I could barely count your bowls.

123
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,440
You're not an ordinary girl.

124
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,680
I concealed my identity for so long.

125
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,720
How did you figure out that I'm an angel?

126
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:20,840
Was it supposed to be funny?

127
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,240
Why?

128
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,440
- Are you making fun of me?
- Easy.

129
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:26,280
- Ouch.
- Oops!

130
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:47,160
How does the school janitor of the year
find time to date a girl?

131
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,280
I wouldn't take that
as a friendly greeting.

132
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,520
I would take that as a dog's bark.

133
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,680
Let's go, Dao.

134
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:06,280
If you don't want to get in trouble,

135
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,080
just back off.

136
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,480
But…

137
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,480
I want some trouble!

138
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,000
- Joe.
- Dao, let's go.

139
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,040
Get him!

140
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,720
Is this the police station?

141
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,120
I would like to file a report.

142
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,240
I saw some teens fighting.

143
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,440
Dao!

144
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,400
- Get him!
- Hey!

145
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,240
- Where are you going?
- Stop!

146
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,280
Hey!

147
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,000
- Don't!
- Where are you going?

148
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:38,920
Dao, get behind me.

149
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,440
Petch!

150
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,200
Stop!

151
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,600
Leave him alone!

152
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,040
Dao, move!

153
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,640
Dao, run! Run!

154
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,760
- At your back!
- Dao, run!

155
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,160
Petch, I'll get help!

156
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:28,640
Help!

157
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,000
Somebody help us!

158
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,360
Please help us.

159
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:38,080
Ake.

160
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:39,720
Are you all right?

161
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,920
Do you know how worried I am?

162
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,200
How did you get here?

163
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:47,040
Our stars always align.
Come, let's go home.

164
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,200
I won't!

165
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:53,440
My friend is being attacked.
I have to save him.

166
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,520
I won't let you. Go home!

167
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,280
- I can't!
- Dao, don't be stubborn.

168
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,760
- Go home.
- I won't!

169
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,720
- Dao!
- I have to save him!

170
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,000
I won't let you.

171
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,680
Just listen to me!

172
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,720
Sir.

173
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,240
We were informed that there was a fight.

174
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:13,520
Yes. There are delinquents
fighting over there.

175
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,280
Okay. Sarge, let's go.

176
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:17,600
Ake.

177
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,840
How could you tell the police
to arrest my friend?

178
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,960
I don't want to hear a word. Go home.

179
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,920
- Ake. Listen!
- Go home!

180
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,320
I don't want to go home! Let me go!

181
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,280
Try me!

182
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:38,040
Joe! How dare you?

183
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:40,200
How dare you?

184
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,240
Stop!

185
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:47,920
Drop the weapon!

186
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,440
Are you a student or a delinquent?

187
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:54,280
- Arrest him.
- Let go!

188
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,400
Are you all right?

189
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:58,760
He started it! Let me go!

190
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,880
Control him.

191
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:05,080
Pull over! I told you to pull over!

192
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:07,360
- Pull--
- Dao! Stop shouting!

193
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,800
The police should be arresting
Petch by now.

194
00:14:11,880 --> 00:14:15,040
How? How did you know he was Petch?

195
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,840
I've got eyes everywhere.

196
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,960
You can't hide anything from me.

197
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:25,440
Ake! You're evil! How could you do that?

198
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,720
- Ake!
- Dao!

199
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,240
I am this evil

200
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,400
because of you.

201
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,400
Don't put the blame on me.

202
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,360
You're evil!

203
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,560
Let go of me!

204
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:40,600
I'm warning you, Dao.

205
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,280
If you keep behaving like this,

206
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:45,840
Petch will only face more consequences.

207
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,240
Are you threatening me?

208
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,640
I'm not.

209
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:50,720
But you can try me.

210
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,000
I want to prove

211
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,000
whether I'm a man of my word.

212
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:15,600
<i>- Sorry, the number you have dialed is not…</i>
- Petch! Why did you turn off your phone?

213
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,560
What is he doing?

214
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,600
I'm starving.

215
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:26,160
His dad should be in bed by now.

216
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,080
Petch?

217
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,520
What are you doing?

218
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,960
I can't find dinner.

219
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,600
Petch.

220
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:14,400
Can you hear me?

221
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,440
Don't push yourself too much.

222
00:16:22,320 --> 00:16:23,280
<i>Thank you.</i>

223
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:28,280
I'm heading to bed.

224
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,360
<i>Thank you.</i>

225
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:44,680
Dear God. Please keep him upstairs.

226
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,160
Shit! Mr. Nop!

227
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:52,800
Dam, you punk!

228
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:54,680
- Dam!
- Shit!

229
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,000
Why are you lying to me?

230
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,880
I'm not.

231
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:02,800
I'm just strategizing
to keep the tiger at home

232
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,359
and let the cub go wild at the concert.

233
00:17:05,440 --> 00:17:06,599
What?

234
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:08,200
Petch is at the concert?

235
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:11,440
Easy. Mr. Nop, easy.

236
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,240
Hello?

237
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:18,960
What's up, Waeng?

238
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,520
What did you just say?

239
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:22,800
You were driving

240
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:24,359
and you saw what?

241
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:26,079
Petch got arrested?

242
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,079
Teen fight?

243
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,200
Thanks, Waeng.

244
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:38,080
Petch.

245
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:41,600
Officer.

246
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,240
I'm his father.

247
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,880
He has no record.

248
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,160
Officer, please give him
some justice here.

249
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:52,960
Why the hell did you arrest my son?

250
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:57,560
Dad, he beat me.

251
00:17:57,640 --> 00:17:59,320
- Are you that tough, huh?
- Hey!

252
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,480
Please speak politely.

253
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:02,000
Why the hell did you push me?

254
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,400
No father wants to see their son get hurt.

255
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:06,560
I am a father too.

256
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,160
Good.

257
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,960
I'll put you two behind bars!

258
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,440
Officer!

259
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,880
I'll file a report to arrest them.

260
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:16,440
They physically assaulted us.

261
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:20,280
Take it easy. It's a teen fight.
It's not a big deal.

262
00:18:20,360 --> 00:18:21,440
What?

263
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,080
How could you say that, Officer?

264
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:26,320
If I have to arrest him,
I have to arrest your son as well.

265
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,440
You can't!

266
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,880
Do you want to be demoted?

267
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,040
Don't you know that I'm friends
with the police captain here?

268
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:35,880
Please watch your tone.

269
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,480
You're threatening
a law enforcement officer.

270
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:39,960
I've already interrogated them.

271
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,000
They have no criminal record.

272
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,760
Most importantly, they're both minors.

273
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:47,280
I don't want them
to have criminal records.

274
00:18:48,120 --> 00:18:49,800
For now, I will give them a warning.

275
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:53,000
But if this happens again,
I'll arrest them.

276
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,560
Thank you, Officer.

277
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:59,320
For the parents, please take care
and lecture your children.

278
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,320
Yes, sir.

279
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:17,440
Dad!

280
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:18,800
Dad!

281
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:23,200
I'd rather you scold or hit me
than give me this silent treatment.

282
00:19:24,280 --> 00:19:25,920
Scolding or hitting

283
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:28,640
cannot regain my trust.

284
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,360
Dad.

285
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,200
Move.

286
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,080
If you don't punish me,

287
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:38,600
I'll do it myself.

288
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:43,120
Petch!

289
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:48,040
What the hell are you doing?

290
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,280
I know

291
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,240
I've let you down.

292
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:53,880
Good.

293
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,240
What do you want me to do?

294
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,760
Swear it to me.

295
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,400
Swear to quit music for good.

296
00:20:05,480 --> 00:20:06,720
What?

297
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:09,360
Everything that happened
was because of music!

298
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,680
You sneaked out to see the concert!

299
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:13,400
- That was not the cause!
- That was the cause!

300
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:15,600
Why did the police arrest you?

301
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:18,400
I was just trying to protect a girl.

302
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:19,560
Don't make excuses!

303
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,960
I'm telling the truth.

304
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:22,840
But you never listen.

305
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,520
This is my last warning to you!

306
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:31,000
Don't let this happen again!

307
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:31,920
Otherwise,

308
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,280
you are no son of mine!

309
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,600
NATEDAO

310
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:42,560
PETCH, REPLY, PLEASE.
I'M SO WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

311
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,840
WHERE ARE YOU? HOW ARE YOU? PLEASE REPLY.

312
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,040
Petch.

313
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,920
ARE YOU SAFE, DAO?

314
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:56,400
I'M SAFE AT HOME. YOU?

315
00:21:57,720 --> 00:22:01,800
POLICE RELEASED ME.
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

316
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:08,520
I WON'T HAVE MUCH TIME TO CHAT.

317
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:12,720
I WISH YOU THE BEST OF LUCK. BYE.

318
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:35,080
Hello! Have you reserved the table, sir?

319
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:36,640
Akekaphol asked to see me.

320
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,480
What's up, little bro?

321
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,120
There you are.

322
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:41,720
What's up, bro?

323
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:44,200
Go upstairs. Akekaphol will see you now.

324
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:48,320
Your reward.

325
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,280
Thank you, sir.

326
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:58,800
I told you.

327
00:22:59,400 --> 00:23:00,760
I'm a man of my word.

328
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:02,920
Thank you

329
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:05,120
for beating the hell out of Petch.

330
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,400
No biggie.

331
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,640
I didn't expect

332
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,400
that you're into Petch's girlfriend too.

333
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,080
What the hell did you just say?

334
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:17,760
Natedao is mine.
She does not belong to Petch!

335
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,280
Sir!

336
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,320
Take it easy.

337
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,200
He is just a kid.

338
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:26,440
It's okay.

339
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,240
I'll take this
as blessed water from an elder.

340
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,000
Good day, sir.

341
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,120
Wait.

342
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:36,680
You still owe me 100,000 baht.

343
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,840
About that…

344
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:42,400
I still can't pay you today, sir.

345
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:46,120
Can you cut me some slack on this debt?

346
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:52,440
Then you must work for me.

347
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:53,680
What work?

348
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:56,040
Do whatever it takes

349
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,120
to kick Petch

350
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,400
out of school.

351
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:04,320
You want me to get him expelled?

352
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,280
Yes.

353
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,440
Make it happen

354
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:09,840
and you will owe me nothing.

355
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:13,360
Do you really mean that?

356
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,320
I am a man of my word.

357
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:19,000
And my enemy

358
00:24:20,640 --> 00:24:22,360
can't sleep with their eyes closed.

359
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,560
Go.

360
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,120
Sir.

361
00:24:44,040 --> 00:24:45,400
You finished your meal?

362
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,440
Yes, ma'am.

363
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:49,160
I'm full from the tasty meal.

364
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:53,480
Thank you so much
for treating me to this breakfast.

365
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:55,840
We should thank you, Ake.

366
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:57,240
You brought Dao home yesterday.

367
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:59,720
You volunteered to drive her
to school this morning as well.

368
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:03,160
Here's Dao.

369
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:09,240
I'd like to skip breakfast.
I'd like to head off to school.

370
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,240
Dao, wait, sweetie.

371
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,960
Wait for Ake.

372
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,400
Why?

373
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:20,080
He will drive you to school.

374
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:24,240
I can go by myself.
I don't want to bother him.

375
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:25,440
Dao.

376
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:27,200
I'm willing to.

377
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,400
Besides,

378
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,720
your parents won't worry

379
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:33,400
that anyone would harm you.

380
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,680
Exactly. We trust Ake.

381
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:39,520
Let him drive you to school.

382
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,440
Dao.

383
00:25:58,360 --> 00:25:59,920
Are you still mad at me?

384
00:26:00,880 --> 00:26:03,000
Why is that punk so special to you?

385
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:06,040
Why do you want to protect him that much?

386
00:26:07,560 --> 00:26:09,840
Petch is not a punk. He is a good man.

387
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:11,200
Dao.

388
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:13,440
You're being too optimistic.

389
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,400
He's just an auto mechanic student.

390
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,640
If you keep seeing him,

391
00:26:18,240 --> 00:26:19,440
aren't you worried

392
00:26:19,960 --> 00:26:21,320
he's just after your money?

393
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:24,640
He is not like that. I trust what I see.

394
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,320
I can see who is good and who is evil.

395
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:34,800
Dao.

396
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:37,320
You can say whatever you want.

397
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:39,000
But I'll tell you this.

398
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:41,920
The man who is best for you is me.

399
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,920
From now on,

400
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:46,920
I won't let you out of my sight.

401
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:13,240
"Somsak Garage is looking for mechanics.

402
00:27:13,320 --> 00:27:15,400
Full-time and part-time vacancies."

403
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:20,320
Petch.

404
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,400
Look.

405
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,680
This garage is looking for mechanics.
Are you interested?

406
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:28,320
Later, man.

407
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:35,640
I fixed it for you.

408
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,400
Really?

409
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:39,760
What?

410
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,680
You're a genius!

411
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:44,960
Don't flatter me.

412
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,160
Check the machine then.

413
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:49,040
I'll go to the restroom.

414
00:27:49,120 --> 00:27:51,560
Thank you, buddy. Oh, my!

415
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:54,920
Flawless.

416
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,840
I've finished.

417
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,040
Ko. Bank.

418
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,560
Asking for daddies?

419
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,120
What do you want?

420
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:29,280
To give you some money. Take it.

421
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,160
Back off. I don't want it.

422
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,680
What the hell?

423
00:28:52,840 --> 00:28:55,800
What? What the hell are you doing?

424
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,040
- Petch!
- Stop!

425
00:28:57,120 --> 00:28:59,000
- Stop!
- Let go of me!

426
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:00,200
What? Petch!

427
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:01,880
- What the hell? Let go!
- Petch! No!

428
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:05,360
- Petch! No!
- What the hell? Let go of me!

429
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:07,600
- Petch! Let me go!
- You let go of me!

430
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:09,640
<i>- You let go of me!</i>
<i>- Petch!</i>

431
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,960
- What the hell?
- Petch! No!

432
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:13,520
- Let go!
- Petch! No!

433
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:16,080
- There! He is bullying them for money!
- Petch!

434
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:18,480
What?

435
00:29:23,480 --> 00:29:26,240
I never expected you to go this far.

436
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:38,000
Sir, I didn't do it.

437
00:29:38,080 --> 00:29:39,680
If you didn't do it,

438
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:43,400
then why do Ko and Bank look like crap?

439
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,440
They tried to frame me, sir.

440
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:46,520
Hey, watch it.

441
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:50,120
Who would hurt them if it wasn't you?

442
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,240
Right.

443
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:53,600
Ko and I refused,

444
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:56,840
so he punched us and tried to stab us.

445
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,720
That's right, sir.

446
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:00,520
Look at us and look at Petch.

447
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:02,120
He doesn't have a single scratch.

448
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:06,520
I've sent you the clip as evidence.

449
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:08,840
It is obvious

450
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:11,480
that Petch is lying.

451
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,520
The evidence was found
in the restroom, sir.

452
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:16,920
Petch.

453
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:18,960
A real man must accept

454
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:21,160
what he has done wrong.

455
00:30:22,200 --> 00:30:24,160
I'm a real man, sir.

456
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,480
I have pride.

457
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,400
I wouldn't do anything evil.

458
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:28,480
All right.

459
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,120
Despite your denial,

460
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:31,840
we have evidence

461
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,520
and witnesses.

462
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:37,200
You're currently on probation, aren't you?

463
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:43,640
Yes.

464
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,280
Rules are rules.

465
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:49,000
You broke the rules during probation.

466
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:52,000
I regret to inform you

467
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,520
that the school can no longer keep you.

468
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:18,280
I got Petch expelled.

469
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:19,680
Great job, Joe.

470
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:21,360
You did a great job.

471
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,560
I hope you won't forget your promise.

472
00:31:23,640 --> 00:31:24,640
Yes.

473
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:27,160
For now,

474
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:28,840
you owe me nothing.

475
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,120
Thank you so much, sir.

476
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:37,640
Why?

477
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,560
Why is my life so messed up?

478
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:43,040
- Petch! Enough!
- I wish you could see him right now.

479
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:44,640
He is so pathetic.

480
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:50,960
Joe, you know what?
This is just the first lesson.

481
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,200
Whoever is my enemy,

482
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,560
he won't have a peaceful life.

483
00:31:56,520 --> 00:32:00,560
If I can't be a professional musician,
I won't give up my dream.

484
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,000
So…

485
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:03,720
What's next?

486
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,640
No idea.

487
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:10,120
I know one thing.

488
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,520
Know what?

489
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,640
If my dad knew that I got expelled,

490
00:32:15,480 --> 00:32:17,280
he'd be devastatingly disappointed.

491
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:21,080
So you must keep this between us.

492
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:23,440
Right. I won't tell him.

493
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,560
Sir?

494
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:41,360
So what exactly is your destination?

495
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:44,520
It is unlikely to have residents here.

496
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:48,200
Just keep going straight. I'll pay.

497
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,320
That is not the problem.

498
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:52,720
I'll take you there for sure.

499
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,440
But this place

500
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:57,160
is unlikely to have people around.

501
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:58,800
It's desolate.

502
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,160
How about this?

503
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:05,920
I'll take you to the main road
and I won't charge you.

504
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,320
Pull over!

505
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,720
- What the hell?
- Pull over!

506
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:19,120
Why are you doing this?

507
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:22,280
I've been jobless for a year.
What other choice do I have?

508
00:33:23,320 --> 00:33:24,560
Oh, boy.

509
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:26,440
Shut up, grandpa!

510
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:28,320
Give me everything you've got!

511
00:33:29,440 --> 00:33:30,760
Hurry.

512
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:44,640
Stop! Stop right now!

513
00:33:44,720 --> 00:33:45,560
Stop!

514
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,440
Go!

515
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:17,280
WELDING AND SHEET METAL SHOP,
AUTO MECHANICS SHOP

516
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,400
Goodbye.

517
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:32,679
Hello?

518
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:38,639
Yes. He is my father.

519
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:41,800
What?

520
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,080
He's hospitalized with a stab wound?

521
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:46,840
Dad.

522
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,679
Thank you so much, Waeng.

523
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:53,040
I really do. I owe you this one.

524
00:34:53,120 --> 00:34:56,159
It's okay, Nop. Take care of yourself.

525
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:58,280
Just pay me back when you can.

526
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:00,520
I will pay you back.

527
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:02,360
Don't you worry.

528
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:05,120
I know. We're brothers.

529
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,360
Petch. There you are, boy.

530
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:09,760
Hello, Mr. Waeng.

531
00:35:09,840 --> 00:35:11,200
- Hello.
- Hello.

532
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:12,120
Hello.

533
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:14,520
Take good care of your dad.

534
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:16,320
I'm heading off for work.

535
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,080
See you, Nop.

536
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:19,760
Call me anytime.

537
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:20,680
Okay.

538
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,320
Thank you so much.

539
00:35:25,760 --> 00:35:26,960
How are you holding up?

540
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:28,880
Better.

541
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:31,120
The doctor stitched my wound already.

542
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:32,480
What a relief!

543
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:34,360
Get well soon, sir.

544
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:37,160
Thank you, Dam.

545
00:35:38,960 --> 00:35:40,480
I have to get better

546
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:42,520
or we'll starve.

547
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:44,360
I heard you and Mr. Waeng.

548
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:47,760
He loaned you some money, didn't he?

549
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:49,680
Yes.

550
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,960
I need some money

551
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:56,000
for my hospital fee, my recovery,
and the loss of income.

552
00:35:57,480 --> 00:36:00,400
I borrowed 30,000 from him.

553
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:02,800
Thirty grand?

554
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,680
That's all right.

555
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:11,000
I'll help you with that.

556
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,280
No.

557
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:15,640
Your duty is to study,

558
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,240
so focus on that.

559
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,400
I'll take care of the rest.

560
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:20,840
But…

561
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:22,960
I…

562
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:28,040
Can I quit school? I want to work.

563
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:30,640
- No!
- Dad.

564
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,400
Petch.

565
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:37,840
I never ask anything of you

566
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:41,080
but to focus on your studies.

567
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:44,160
You must graduate.

568
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:45,600
If not,

569
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,960
then you are no son of mine.

570
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:07,440
Come on, man. Don't stress yourself out.

571
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,840
Dad cannot know.

572
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:12,640
You heard him.

573
00:37:12,720 --> 00:37:14,120
I did.

574
00:37:14,200 --> 00:37:16,000
He has high expectations of you.

575
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:17,880
How long will you keep it from him?

576
00:37:17,960 --> 00:37:18,800
Until…

577
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,960
I can get into another school.

578
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:22,520
In the meantime,

579
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,280
I'll look for a job.

580
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:27,400
What job?

581
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:32,240
Mechanic at that garage.

582
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,480
Here is the address.

583
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,200
Let's go.

584
00:37:50,320 --> 00:37:51,240
Dao.

585
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:54,200
Come review lessons with me.

586
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:56,280
Okay. I'll be there.

587
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,520
Okay.

588
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:29,680
Can I keep the tickets?

589
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:32,240
Why?

590
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:34,120
Just hand it to me.

591
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:44,120
FIRST TIME ON THE BUS

592
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:05,840
This is it.

593
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:07,160
Hey.

594
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:09,240
Come on, man. Go get it!

595
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,240
Let's go.

596
00:39:38,720 --> 00:39:40,040
Excellent.

597
00:39:40,120 --> 00:39:40,960
Yes.

598
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:44,760
Not only does Petch know
every piece of equipment,

599
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:47,800
but he also scores
the highest in our class.

600
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:50,040
He is the top student.

601
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:51,760
But…

602
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:53,560
I just got expelled, sir.

603
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:58,760
Petch! Are you out of your mind?

604
00:39:58,840 --> 00:40:00,600
He might reject you.

605
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,840
I don't want to lie.
I feel better with the truth.

606
00:40:05,360 --> 00:40:06,560
Are you crazy?

607
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:11,160
Sir, he got expelled

608
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:14,200
because he was framed.

609
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:15,160
Enough!

610
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:18,000
I don't want to hear a word.

611
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,440
That's a real man.

612
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:26,800
A real man accepts his mistakes.

613
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,240
You've got the job at my garage, Petch.

614
00:40:29,840 --> 00:40:31,160
I am accepted?

615
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:33,920
Thank you, sir!

616
00:40:35,160 --> 00:40:36,920
I can't believe it.

617
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:38,960
At this garage,

618
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:40,480
we're like family.

619
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:43,280
You get a salary and OT.

620
00:40:43,360 --> 00:40:45,000
We'll discuss this with the finance team.

621
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,480
All right. And…

622
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,960
When should I start?

623
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:51,640
Tomorrow.

624
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,720
- Tomorrow?
- Yes.

625
00:40:54,640 --> 00:40:56,760
Thank you, sir! Thank you!

626
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:58,600
Thank you!

627
00:40:58,680 --> 00:40:59,640
Keep up the good work.

628
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:18,440
I've prepared your breakfast.

629
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:21,160
Don't forget to take
your after-meal medication.

630
00:41:25,440 --> 00:41:27,040
Thank you, son.

631
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,800
You must rest until your wound is healed.

632
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:32,680
Don't move too much.

633
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,320
I know.

634
00:41:35,360 --> 00:41:36,440
Better hurry for school

635
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,200
or you'll be late.

636
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:41,880
What?

637
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:44,920
Why are you staring at me like that?

638
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:47,160
Nothing.

639
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,480
I'm just worried about you.

640
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:53,440
I'm afraid
that you'll be out driving a taxi.

641
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:57,000
Oh, boy.

642
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:59,320
You're just like your mother.

643
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:03,320
Always caring about everyone but yourself.

644
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:05,960
Don't worry.

645
00:42:06,560 --> 00:42:08,720
Do your best at school.

646
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:11,080
Focus on your studies.

647
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:13,200
My head mechanic.

648
00:42:16,240 --> 00:42:17,080
All right, Dad.

649
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,760
I'm heading out.

650
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:30,400
What?

651
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:32,160
Who just liked Petch's post?

652
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:35,000
She looks familiar. Oh, my!

653
00:42:35,080 --> 00:42:37,400
She is Young Miss Angel.

654
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:42,080
Withdraw money without a debit card,

655
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:48,280
but why did your heart
fall hard for that girl?

656
00:42:49,360 --> 00:42:50,400
What girl?

657
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:51,320
What?

658
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:52,840
You don't know?

659
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:55,440
That is why I'm asking.

660
00:42:55,520 --> 00:42:57,200
Look.

661
00:42:59,080 --> 00:43:00,560
NATEDAO

662
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:03,040
Now, you're stunned!

663
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:08,120
I've been offline for days and now,
I see big news the second I go online.

664
00:43:08,200 --> 00:43:11,200
When did it happen between you two?

665
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:13,560
Us two? What? No!

666
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:15,240
You're keeping your cool.

667
00:43:15,320 --> 00:43:16,400
Stop.

668
00:43:16,920 --> 00:43:18,440
Stop making fun of me.

669
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:22,920
If there was nothing,
then why did Ms. Natedao like your post?

670
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,040
Look.

671
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:25,560
Well…

672
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:29,440
We met at The Rock Concert.
There was nothing more.

673
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:32,920
Petch, you're so bad

674
00:43:33,760 --> 00:43:34,960
at lying.

675
00:43:36,200 --> 00:43:38,920
Your ears are all red right now!

676
00:43:40,880 --> 00:43:42,080
What am I supposed to say?

677
00:43:43,400 --> 00:43:46,240
Just tell me, so that I can cheer you up.

678
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:48,840
She was the one who gave me money
to repair my motorbike

679
00:43:48,920 --> 00:43:50,560
and treated you to noodles.

680
00:43:52,520 --> 00:43:54,080
You're a lucky man.

681
00:43:54,160 --> 00:43:56,520
She is pretty

682
00:43:56,600 --> 00:43:58,080
and kind.

683
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:00,880
Stop deluding yourself.

684
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:03,120
Listen.

685
00:44:04,040 --> 00:44:06,480
Ms. Natedao's family is wealthy.

686
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:09,880
My dad is a taxi driver.
I barely have money to eat.

687
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:12,160
We come from different classes.

688
00:44:13,720 --> 00:44:14,560
Besides,

689
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:18,560
making money and lying to my dad

690
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:20,720
are giving me enough of a headache.

691
00:44:21,560 --> 00:44:23,600
Just stop talking nonsense.

692
00:44:24,920 --> 00:44:26,120
You're hiding your feelings.

693
00:44:26,200 --> 00:44:27,160
Ready to go?

694
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:28,120
Yes.

695
00:44:32,480 --> 00:44:33,640
She never liked my posts.

696
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:34,680
Not a word.

697
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:36,480
She only liked yours.

698
00:44:36,560 --> 00:44:37,400
Quiet.

699
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:53,680
WHY ARE YOU GHOSTING ME?

700
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:57,560
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

701
00:45:27,840 --> 00:45:29,200
NATEDAO

702
00:45:32,400 --> 00:45:33,240
Dao.

703
00:46:01,520 --> 00:46:03,520
Why can't I visit Petch's account?

704
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:05,760
THIS PAGE IS NOT AVAILABLE

705
00:46:11,080 --> 00:46:13,520
Pin, Prae. I have a question.

706
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:14,760
Okay.

707
00:46:14,840 --> 00:46:19,560
If you can't access or search
your friend's account,

708
00:46:20,160 --> 00:46:22,080
is it because they blocked you?

709
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:25,000
They probably deactivated their account.

710
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:26,960
Deactivated?

711
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:30,400
You mean they quit it for good?

712
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:31,800
Yes, that's right.

713
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:34,920
Whose account are you talking about?

714
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:36,160
Can I take a look?

715
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:39,360
No one. I was just curious.

716
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:40,840
See you later.

717
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:43,040
- You're leaving?
- Yes. Bye-bye.

718
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:47,600
What is with her?

719
00:46:47,680 --> 00:46:49,360
- She is always in a rush.
- Yeah.

720
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:55,160
Ake.

721
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:08,440
- Pin, Prae. Can you do me a favor?
- What?

722
00:47:08,520 --> 00:47:10,040
I'll help you review every subject.

723
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:12,400
That's perfect. What can we do for you?

724
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:15,640
Ake.

725
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:18,000
Hello.

726
00:47:18,080 --> 00:47:19,040
- Hello.
- Hello.

727
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:20,800
I'm here to pick up Dao.

728
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:23,600
Don't rush home yet.

729
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:26,960
Please treat us to some dinner.

730
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:30,240
That's right.
There's a new diner near our school.

731
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:32,080
People said the food is super tasty.

732
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:33,480
Well…

733
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:36,320
I'll let Dao decide. What would you like?

734
00:47:36,400 --> 00:47:38,920
The diner near our school.

735
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:40,200
But…

736
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:41,240
But?

737
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:45,480
I have a meeting
for the school's English content online.

738
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:49,600
You can take Pin and Prae for dinner
while waiting for me.

739
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:50,880
Is that all right?

740
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:54,200
Yes. I'll catch up with you later.

741
00:47:56,480 --> 00:47:57,880
- Okay.
- Let's go.

742
00:47:57,960 --> 00:47:59,880
- Let's go.
- Go!

743
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,400
Excuse me.

744
00:48:32,600 --> 00:48:33,960
Do you know a man named Petch?

745
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:36,920
Are you looking for Petch?

746
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:45,360
It's you.

747
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,360
I'm Damrong. Petch's friend.

748
00:48:50,080 --> 00:48:53,440
That's great. Do you know where he is?

749
00:48:53,520 --> 00:48:55,320
I can't contact him at all.

750
00:49:17,080 --> 00:49:20,920
Only a lunatic like you
would reject Ms. Natedao.

751
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:22,760
She is too good for me.

752
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:25,560
NEXT EPISODE

753
00:49:25,640 --> 00:49:29,720
Why did you lower your standards
and befriend a riffraff like that?

754
00:49:30,800 --> 00:49:32,360
But you're heartless!

755
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:34,560
I came here today

756
00:49:37,760 --> 00:49:39,400
because I'll be at a piano contest

757
00:49:42,040 --> 00:49:44,680
and I want emotional support
from you the most.

758
00:49:58,480 --> 00:50:03,480
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

759
00:50:04,760 --> 00:50:09,840
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

760
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:16,560
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

761
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:21,480
<i>But never reaching you</i>

762
00:50:22,360 --> 00:50:26,960
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

763
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:33,240
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

764
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:39,920
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

765
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:45,320
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

766
00:50:47,320 --> 00:50:51,960
<i>You are out of reach</i>

767
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:57,680
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

768
00:50:59,760 --> 00:51:04,560
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

769
00:51:04,640 --> 00:51:09,800
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

770
00:51:10,680 --> 00:51:15,200
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

771
00:51:16,400 --> 00:51:21,560
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

772
00:51:22,640 --> 00:51:27,600
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

773
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:34,280
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

774
00:51:34,360 --> 00:51:36,080
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
